From bae85847596e50caccf1b6f3dbd8c53c64eb1091 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mateo de los Rios <mdelosrios@nurixtx.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Apr 2026 12:40:05 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] chore: v1.0 release-hardening pass before desktop
 distribution

Pre-production review fixes across the Windows desktop build:

- Windows .bat: fix Unix redirects (replace '>/' + 'dev/null' with '>nul')
  in Start Jojo Bot.bat and Stop Jojo Bot.bat
- RAG: drop scrambled DOCUMENT_TITLES dict; derive titles from filenames in
  both ingest.py and retriever.py (belt-and-suspenders fallback for any
  stale metadata already in ChromaDB)
- Version sync to 1.0.0 across package.json, package-lock.json, main.py
  health endpoint, README.md, CHANGELOG.md
- config.py: remove os.chdir side-effect at import time; validators anchor
  relative paths to the app dir instead
- main.py: bind backend to 127.0.0.1 by default; opt-in 0.0.0.0 via
  JOJO_DEV_LAN=1 for LAN testing. Production builds always stay local.
- main.py: cap _rate_limit dict at 10_000 keys with stale-key purge to
  prevent unbounded growth over long uptimes
- Kill cloud deploy artifacts: remove railway.toml and src/backend/Dockerfile
  (product is Windows desktop only; no hosted backend)
- Ship kb_manifest.json regenerated with filename-derived titles
- SettingsPanel: surface real error when KB endpoint is unreachable
- generator.py: expand system_prompt.txt candidate paths for frozen exe

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
